  "prompt": "Which is a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center in Calhoun County AL?",
  "response": "Finding a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center in Calhoun County, AL, depends on your specific needs, such as treatment programs, insurance coverage, and personal preferences. Here are a few options to consider:\n\n### 1. **Bradford Health Services - Oxford, AL**  \n   - Location: Oxford, AL (within Calhoun County)  \n   - Specializes in addiction treatment for adults and adolescents.  \n   - Offers inpatient, outpatient, and aftercare programs.  \n   - Focuses on individualized treatment plans, including therapy and relapse prevention.  \n   - Website: [Bradford Health Services](https://www.bradfordhealth.com)  \n\n### 2. **The Breakthrough Recovery Outreach Center**  \n   - Location: Jacksonville, AL (near Calhoun County)  \n   - Offers faith-based and holistic recovery programs.  \n   - Provides inpatient and outpatient services, including counseling and support groups.  \n   - Website: [The Breakthrough Recovery Outreach Center](https://www.breakthroughrecoveryoutreach.org)  \n\n### 3. **Northeast Alabama Regional Medical Center (RMC) Behavioral Health**  \n   - Location: Anniston, AL (Calhoun County)  \n   - Provides inpatient and outpatient mental health and substance abuse treatment.  \n   - Offers detoxification, individual/group therapy, and medication management.  \n   - Website: [RMC Health System](https://www.rmccares.org)  \n\n### 4. **New Perspectives at High Point**  \n   - Location: Anniston, AL (Calhoun County)  \n   - Offers inpatient detox and residential treatment for substance abuse.  \n   - Focuses on dual diagnosis (mental health and addiction) treatment.  \n   - Website: [New Perspectives](https://www.newperspectivesrehab.com)  \n\n### How to Choose the Right Center:  \n- **Insurance:** Verify if the facility accepts your insurance plan.  \n- **Programs:** Look for centers that offer evidence-based therapies, such as cognitive-behavioral therapy (CBT) or 12-step programs.  \n- **Accreditation:** Ensure the facility is licensed and accredited by reputable organizations.  \n- **Reviews:** Read reviews or testimonials from former patients.  \n\nFor more options, you can contact the **Alabama Department of Mental Health** or use the **Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration (SAMHSA)** website to find treatment centers near you: [SAMHSA Treatment Locator](https://findtreatment.samhsa.gov).  \n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
